<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure10>
    dc:description "Figure 10. Distribution of Novochares abbreviatus species group A N. abbreviatus: examined specimens (red) and literature / unconfirmed records (blue) B N. oculatus: examined specimens (red) and literature / unconfirmed records (blue) C N. pallipes (red), N. latus (yellow), N. baca (blue), N. pilatus (green)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881177" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure2>
    dc:description "Figure 2. Phylogeny of Novochares spp. Part 2: Novochares abbreviatus species group. Inferred from COI and 28 S combined sequence data. Numbers next to taxon names are extraction numbers (see Table 1)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881169" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure3>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Aedeagi of the Novochares abbreviatus species group along with schematic representations of the whole, the parameres (in blue), and the dorsal (in yellow) and ventral (in red) plates of the median lobe A N. abbreviatus B N. oculatus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881170" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure7>
    dc:description "Figure 7. Dorsal habitus of Novochares spp. A N. abbreviatus B N. pilatus C N. minor D N. tenedor." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881174" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure8>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Aedeagi of the Novochares abbreviatus species group A-L N. abbreviatus A-C Nicaragua D-F Argentina G-I Venezuela J-L Guyana M-O N. latus P-R N. pilatus A, D, G, J, M, P dorsal view B, E, H, K, N, Q ventral view C, F, I, L, O, R lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881175" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.1171.104142.figure9>
    dc:description "Figure 9. Aedeagi and habitus of the Novochares abbreviatus species group A-E N. oculatus: A-C aedeagus, Mexico D, E paralectotype from Guatemala D aedeagus E habitus F-K miscellaneous forms of aedeagi in the Novochares abbreviatus species group F, G Argentina H, I Venezuela J, K Bolivia L, M, R N. pallipes N, O N. baca A, D, F, H, J, L, N dorsal view B, M ventral view C, G, I, K, O lateral view R oblique view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/881176" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

